           MEDIA ADVISORY: REAC/TS hosts 5th International  Symposium on the Medical Basis for Radiation Accident Preparedness 
       
           FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
            June 27, 2011 
          FY11-35 
           Who:  Radiation Emergency Assistance Center/Training Site  
          What: REAC/TSÑa program of the Oak Ridge Institute for Science and EducationÑ
is hosting a three-day symposium titled the  5th International REAC/TS Symposium on the Medical Basis for Radiation Accident Preparedness.  

 The symposium will bring together more than 30 international, medical experts to discuss the advances in the diagnosis and management of radiation emergencies and illnesses.
 
 The  National Nuclear Security Administration's   Associate Administrator for Emergency Operations Joseph J. Krol, Jr., Rear Admiral, U.S. Navy (Retired)  will serve as the symposium's keynote speaker.  
 The symposium begins on Sept. 27 and ends on Sept. 29. A registration fee of $250 is required for each participant. 
 
 ORISE designates this live activity for a maximum of 20.5 AMA PRA Category 1 Credit(s)ª. Physicians should claim only the credit commensurate with the extent of their participation in the activity. ORISE is accredited by the  Accreditation Council for Continuing Medical Education (ACCME)  to provide continuing medical education for physicians. ORISE takes responsibility for the content, quality and scientific integrity of this CME activity.  
 REAC/TS is supported by the NNSA. ORISE is an institute of the  U.S. Department of Energy  and is managed by  Oak Ridge Associated Universities .  
 When: Sept. 27-29, 2011;
8 a.m. Ð 5:15 p.m. daily
 
 Where:  Hilton Miami Downtown , 1601 Biscayne Blvd., Miami, FL 33132 
(305) 374-0000  
 Symposium Contact:  REAC/TS Symposium Website  
  (865) 576-3131 




           
         
